metadata.name: NEC Networks & System Integration Corporation
metadata.description: NEC Networks & System Integration Corporation provides planning, consulting, system design and integration, construction, and installation services in Japan and internationally. It operates through Digital Solutions Business, Network Infrastructures Business, and Engineering & Support Services Business segments. The Digital Solutions Business segment offers systems and services for information and communications technology (ICT), such as corporate networks and IT using digital technologies, which includes artificial intelligence, the Internet of Things, and robotic process automation. The Network Infrastructures Business segment builds systems and provides services for the network infrastructure for public use, including networks for telecom carriers, and ICT infrastructure for national and local governments, as well as broadcasters. The Engineering & Support Services Business segment offers maintenance, operating and monitoring, outsourcing, and other support services, as well as construction for ICT systems and services. It's products include telephony servers, video conferencing systems, routers, switches, network testers, interface converters, load balancers, accelerators, internet traffic, SSL-VPN access firewalls, unauthorized access detection, authentication systems, operation and maintenance, spam blocking, physical security, log management industry and task-specific applications, and software. The company operates through a service network of approximately 400 locations in Japan. NEC Networks & System Integration Corporation was founded in 1953 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
